GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 52
Short Title: Protect Those Who Serve & Protect Act of 2025. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Hastings, Cotham, Miller, and Pyrtle (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: State and Local Government, if favorable, Judiciary 2, if favorable, Rules,
Calendar, and Operations of the House
February 5, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT ENACTING THE PROTECT THOSE WHO SERVE AND PROTECT ACT OF 2025.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. This act shall be known as the "Protect Those Who Serve and Protect
5 Act of 2025."
6 SECTION 2. Article 8 of Chapter 14 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
7 a new section to read:
8 "§ 14-34.7A. Assault on a public safety officer, law enforcement agency animal, or search
9 and rescue animal by throwing, spraying, or otherwise projecting water or other
10 substances.
11 (a) Definition. – The following definitions apply in this section:
12 (1) Law enforcement agency animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
13 (2) Public safety officer. – Any of the following:
14 a. A law enforcement officer.
15 b. A probation or parole officer.
16 c. A person who is employed at (i) a detention facility, as defined in
17 G.S. 143B-805, or (ii) any other detention facility operated under the
18 jurisdiction of the State or a local government.
19 d. A firefighter or rescue squad worker.
20 e. An emergency medical services personnel, as defined in
21 G.S. 131E-155.
22 f. A hospital employee, medical practice employee, licensed health care
23 provider, individual under contract to provide services at a hospital or
24 medical practice, hospital security personnel, or other emergency
25 health care provider not otherwise covered under sub-subdivision e. of
26 this subdivision.
27 g. A member of the North Carolina National Guard.
28 h. A member of any branch of the Armed Forces of the United States.
29 i. A juvenile court counselor or chief court counselor, as those terms are
30 defined in G.S. 143B-805.
31 j. An employee or volunteer at a school, as those terms are defined in
32 subdivision (6) of subsection (c) of G.S. 14-33.
33 (3) Search and rescue animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
*H52-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (b) Offense and Punishment. – Unless covered under some other provision of law
2 providing greater punishment, a person is guilty of a Class I felony if the person commits an
3 assault or battery on either of the following by throwing, spraying, or otherwise projecting, or
4 causing to be thrown, sprayed, or otherwise projected, water or any other substance at:
5 (1) A public safety officer (i) while the public safety officer is discharging or
6 attempting to discharge his or her official duties or (ii) because of the victim's
7 status as a public safety officer.
8 (2) A law enforcement agency animal or a search and rescue animal (i) while the
9 animal is in the performance of its duty or (ii) because of the animal's status
10 as a law enforcement agency animal or search and rescue animal."
11 SECTION 3. G.S. 14-34.8 reads as rewritten:
12 "§ 14-34.8. Criminal use of laser device.
13 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
14 (1) Laser. – Light amplification by stimulated emission of radiation.
15 (2) Law enforcement agency animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
16 (3) Public safety officer. – As defined in G.S. 14-34.7A.
17 (4) Search and rescue animal. – As defined in G.S. 14-163.1.
18 (b) It is unlawful to intentionally point a laser device while the device is emitting a laser
19 beam at:
20 (1) Any of the following A public safety officer (i) while the person is in the
21 performance of his or her duties:duties or (ii) because of the person's status as
22 a public safety officer.
23 a. A law enforcement officer.
24 b. A probation or parole officer.
25 c. A person whose employment duties include the custody,
26 transportation, or management of persons who are detained or
27 confined to a detention facility, youth development center, or
28 correctional institution operated under the jurisdiction of the State or
29 a local government.
30 d. A firefighter.
31 e. An emergency medical technician or other emergency health care
32 provider.
33 f. A member of the North Carolina National Guard.
34 g. A member of any branch of the Armed Forces of the United States.
35 h. Court counselors whose employment duties include intake, probation,
36 post-release supervision, and court supervision services of juveniles.
37 (2) The head or face of any person not covered under subdivision (1) of this
38 subsection.
39 (3) A law enforcement agency animal or a search and rescue animal (i) while the
40 animal is in the performance of its duty.duty or (ii) because of the animal's
41 status as a law enforcement agency animal or search and rescue animal.
42 …."
43 SECTION 4. G.S. 14-32 reads as rewritten:
44 "§ 14-32. Felonious assault with deadly weapon with intent to kill or inflicting serious
45 injury; punishments.
46 …
47 (d) Any Unless covered under some other provision of law providing greater punishment,
48 any person who assaults an emergency worker a public safety officer with a deadly weapon and
49 inflicts serious injury shall be punished as a Class D felon.
