1 Guard while he or she is discharging or attempting to discharge his or her official duties and
2 inflicts serious bodily injury on the member.
3 (b) Unless covered under some other provision of law providing greater punishment, a
4 person is guilty of a Class E felony if the person assaults a person who is employed at a detention
5 facility operated under the jurisdiction of the State or a local government while the employee is
6 in the performance of the employee's duties and inflicts serious bodily injury on the employee.
7 (c) Unless covered under some other provision of law providing greater punishment, a
8 person is guilty of a Class H felony if the person does any of the following:
9 (1) Assaults a law enforcement officer, probation officer, or parole officer while
10 the officer is discharging or attempting to discharge his or her official duties
11 and inflicts physical injury on the officer.
12 (2) Assaults a person who is employed at a detention facility operated under the
13 jurisdiction of the State or a local government while the employee is in the
14 performance of the employee's duties and inflicts physical injury on the
15 employee.
16 (3) Assaults a member of the North Carolina National Guard while he or she is
17 discharging or attempting to discharge his or her official duties and inflicts
18 physical injury on the member.violates subsection (a) of this section and
